      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ABSCONDING (2) has an excellent record over this journey having never missed the placings in six starts, including five wins. Scored by 1.75 lengths last time (18.88) in a NG over 340m at Bulli. Looks suited and should go close. FEDERAL SNIPER (7) shapes well after a good run last time, finishing second in a NG at Maitland in 22.21. Rates a leading chance if runs up to latest. LARNIE'S MAGIC (1) won again in quick time after running them ragged to make it two on end at Gosford over 388m (22.41). Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. In form and can go on with it. MCKEON (5) gave nothing else a chance most recently. That form reads well.",
